[node name="RichTextLabel" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Background/About MEME"]
layout_mode = 2
theme_override_colors/default_color = Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
theme_override_fonts/normal_font = ExtResource("2_2vj31")
theme_override_fonts/bold_font = ExtResource("1_vsc3h")
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 30
theme_override_font_sizes/bold_font_size = 35
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "
Trunk Tales was created in collaboration with the Management and Ecology of Malaysian Elephants (MEME), a research initiative by the University of Nottingham Malaysia and Department of Wildlife and National Parks of Peninsular Malaysia (PERHILITAN). MEME focuses on studying the behaviour and ecology of Asian elephants in Peninsular Malaysia, with the goal of developing evidence-based solutions for their conservation.

Learn more about MEME: https://www.meme-elephants.org

The original Trunk Tales board game was designed by MEME to raise awareness about human-elephant conflict and the importance of balancing the needs of communities, plantation owners, and conservationists. Through gameplay, players can explore how different decisions impact coexistence between humans and elephants.

Building on the success of the physical board game, this digital version makes Trunk Tales more accessible to a wider audience. It also introduces AI-powered players, allowing users to play solo while still learning about real-world conservation challenges. The goal is to educate and inspire players to understand how informed decisions and community involvement can lead to positive environmental outcomes."
fit_content = true
